# No Blocking I/O on the World Owner

In Dragonfly v0.11, callbacks passed to `World.Do` / `player.Do` /
`player.DoAfter`, handler methods, and `cmd.Command.Run` execute on the
**world's owner goroutine**. Anything blocking that runs there freezes world
ticks for every player and has been observed to surface runtime crashes inside
`net/http`.

Never call `world.Call` / `player.Call` / `Task.Wait` from inside an owner
callback — that deadlocks the owner on itself.

## The rule

Inside any of the following contexts, do **not** call HTTP clients, sleep,
wait on channels, hold long mutexes, or do disk I/O:

- `w.Do(func(tx *world.Tx) { ... })`
- `player.Do(handle, func(tx *world.Tx, p *player.Player) { ... })`
- `player.DoAfter(handle, delay, func(tx *world.Tx, p *player.Player) { ... })`
- `cmd.Command.Run(src, output, *world.Tx)`
- `*world.Tx`-receiving callbacks generally

## Pattern: capture first, I/O off-owner, apply via Do

When you need both data from a player **and** an HTTP/disk call:

```go
// ❌ BAD - HTTP call blocks the world owner
player.Do(handle, func(_ *world.Tx, p *player.Player) {
    resp, err := moderation.GlobalService().InflictionOfXUID(p.XUID()) // blocks!
    // ...apply state...
})
```

```go
// ✅ GOOD - capture cheaply on owner, do I/O off-thread, re-enter with Do
xuid := p.XUID() // or pass xuid already captured before scheduling
handle := p.H()

go func() {
    resp, err := moderation.GlobalService().InflictionOfXUID(xuid)
    if err != nil || resp == nil {
        return
    }
    player.Do(handle, func(_ *world.Tx, p *player.Player) {
        // apply resp to p
    })
}()
```

Off-owner code that needs a synchronous result may use
`player.Call(ctx, handle, ...)` / `world.Call(ctx, w, ...)`. Never await those
from inside an owner callback.

## Pattern: command Run methods

`cmd.Command.Run` runs on the owner when the source is world-attached. `tx` may
be nil for console sources — nil-check before using it. Disconnect / mutate the
victim inline, but fire HTTP sync to external services from a goroutine.

```go
// ❌ BAD
func (k Kick) Run(src cmd.Source, o *cmd.Output, _ *world.Tx) {
    moderation.GlobalService().AddInfliction(...) // blocks the owner
    victim.Disconnect(...)
}

// ✅ GOOD
func (k Kick) Run(src cmd.Source, o *cmd.Output, _ *world.Tx) {
    name := victim.Name()
    go func() {
        if err := moderation.GlobalService().AddInfliction(...); err != nil {
            slog.Default().Error("kick sync failed", "target", name, "error", err)
        }
    }()
    victim.Disconnect(...)
}
```

## Reference implementations

- `pokebedrock/session/ranks.go` (`rankWorker`) — HTTP runs on the worker
  goroutine; `player.Do` is used only for popups, messages, and `SetNameTag`.
- `pokebedrock/session/inflictions.go` (`processInflictionRequest`) — XUID is
  captured before enqueue, HTTP runs off-owner, `player.Do` applies effects.
